{{Infobox football league season |competition=[[Venezuelan Primera División]] |season=[[1964 in Venezuelan football|1964]] |winners=[[Deportivo Galicia|Galicia]] (1st title) |relegated= |continentalcup1= |continentalcup1 qualifiers= |continentalcup2= |continentalcup2 qualifiers= |matches= |total goals= |league topscorer= |biggest home win= |biggest away win= |highest scoring= |longest wins = |longest unbeaten = |longest losses = |highest attendance = |lowest attendance = |average attendance = |prevseason=[[1963 Venezuelan Primera División season|1963]] |nextseason=[[1965 Venezuelan Primera División season|1965]] }}
The '''1964 season of the [[Venezuelan Primera División]]''', the top category of [[Venezuela]]n football, was played by 6 teams. The national champions were [[Deportivo Galicia|Galicia]].
