{{Infobox Cycling race report | name = 2005 Vuelta a Venezuela | image = | image_caption = | date = August 29 &ndash; September 11 | series = | stages = 14 | distance = 1983.9 | unit = km | time = 50h 38' 59" | speed = 39.1709 | first = [[José Chacón Díaz]] | first_nat = VEN | first_team = Gobernación del Estado Bolívar | first_color = red | second = [[Artur Garcia Rincon|Artur Garcia]] | second_nat = VEN | second_team = Loteria del Táchira | third = [[Iván Castillo (cyclist)|Iván Castillo]] | third_nat = VEN | third_team = Gobernacíon del Zulía | points = [[Gil Cordovés]] | points_nat = CUB | points_team = Gobernacíon del Zulía | mountains = [[José Alirio Contreras]] | mountains_nat = VEN | mountains_team = Gobernación de Lara Alcaldía | team = Lotería del Táchira | previous = [[2004 Vuelta a Venezuela|2004]] | next = [[2006 Vuelta a Venezuela|2006]] }}
The 42nd edition of the annual '''[[Vuelta a Venezuela]]''' was held from August 29 to September 11, 2005. The stage race started in [[Guanare]], and ended in [[Carúpano]].
